  I think it could be more useful if, when a project is selected, that  project is displayed with its associated issues  could be displayed in Sprint view rather than displaying a board related to the project..

This is my understanding of how it currently works  I have a project called Project X  Firmware and another called Project X Software.  Each of these projects has issues associated with it’s specific code base, but they are related.   Each has a different engineer working on it.  We also have other projects and different teams. So I have a board associated with Project X Firmwre and Project X software, call it board X, and a board that associates Projects X,Y,Z, call it Board XYZ.   When we do our sprint wrap ups we use the Board XYZ.  When we have discussions in day to day activities we might want to just discuss Project X firmware or Project X Software, or both (which we  use a Board X view for).  If I select Project X, I get Board X,  I get either a Board I created that is a mirror of the project Project Firmware X, or that has Project X Firmware and Project X software issues on it, depending on which I selected last from the "view all boards".    .  It seems to me there is really no purpose in selecting project views the way it is.  But a project view is more intuitive if you just want to look at views related to the project.

Now that I understand how it works we certainly can find work arounds using filters.  But I think it would be more useful if Projects just gave the list of issues associated with that project and the same Backlog -> Sprint-> Chart  selections on the left.

